THE ROLE
Expand all
•	Pro-actively generating leads and establishing a solid network across the Corporate Finance & CFO Services industry.
•	Calling, arranging and attending meetings with prospective clients in the region.
•	Negotiating contracts and closing agreements with clients.
•	Managing the entire recruitment process and prioritizing workload.
•	Qualifying client requisitions by interacting with all the stakeholders.
•	Implementing a diverse range of talent acquisition and candidate attraction strategies catered to client requisitions, these include direct headhunting & executive search, job advertising and database scanning
•	Conducting on-going market research and mapping across the Corporate Finance & CFO Services industry to identify prospective clients and remain up-to-date with market developments.
•	Conducting in-depth telephonic and face-to-face interviews, as well as candidate assessments.
•	Keeping record of all activities using the company’s internal software.
•	Remaining up-to-date with trends and techniques in recruitment and executive search
•	Undergoing monthly reviews and quarterly Appraisals
•	Reaching assigned KPIs and Financial Targets
•	Undergoing continuous in-house and professional training
REQUIREMENTS
Required Behaviors:
•	 Extrovert
•	 Entrepreneurial mind-set
•	 Strong networker with high ability to build relationships
•	 Customer focused
•	 High negotiation and communication skills
•	 Natural salesmanship
•	 Organized with a high ability to multitask and manage workloads
•	 Culturally sound
•	 Targets & results-driven
•	 Pro-active with a win-win attitude
•	 Go getter
•	 A strong desire to excel in Executive Search
Skill Requirements:
•	3-5 years of experience in sales and business development with Corporate Finance & CFO Services industry; alternatively working within a renowned executive search or headhunting firm with a proven track record of billings.
•	 Expertise in dealing with different economic services provided by financial institutions such as banks, insurance, accounting firm, asset and wealth management firm, real estate, private equity & venture capital and forex.
•	 Excellent success stories in developing successful relationship with clients.
•	 Proven experience in working across highly competitive environments
ABOUT THE COMPANY
Offshore Recruitment Services specialise in the recruitment of in all aspects of offshore vacancies for all levels of permanent, temporary and contract positions.
Whether a client is searching for a highly skilled candidate, looking to head hunt a specific individual, a team of contractors for a project or management of gifted personnel, we are ready and have a proven track record of meeting such requirements.
Offshore Recruitment Services was formed with the specific aim of providing a quality service to link key candidates to our clients. We find the right people for your business.
